or COF.  And if a chanter casts a haste spell on them, it simply overwrites the items effect if it's a better haste!!  so if you put these 2 together (let's say an FBSS with the eyepatch of plunder)(eyepatch of plunder which is actually pretty easy to obtain considering it's awesome melee stats, not uber hard at all, just uber long camps).  You have a tank with 40% haste, and in a battle, that's ALOT of dmg.  Trust me.  Plus from what I've seen, there are MANY more tank and melee'er quests than there are caster quests (well they are more item dependant) but their items make them SO much better than us, that as a whole they're a better class because they are EXPECTED to have certain items by a certain level (when was the last time you saw a warrior above 30 without at least an FBSS?).  There are no items a caster is expected to have, because no one item can make a SIGNIFICANT difference in a casters usability, this might have supposedly changed with the epic's, but as everyone can see, the wizard's epic is the ONLY one that ONLY helps the wizard and in NO way directly helps the group, either with dmg or with buffing the group (at least bards and chanters can help buff others as well as themselves).  Wizards as a class are vastly neglected, and since we're so dependant on VI to make us a effective class instead of the uber loot they put in the game (there's only a handful of items that will significantly distinguish one wizard from another such as the robe and orb of torrefaction or other such DD items), that we must plead with them to fix us so people will want us again.  I put my faith in VI to make my character wanted in a group instead of going the easy twinkable route where items make you wanted.  Apparently my hard work hasn't paid off and won't pay off ever.  In the next couple patches prepare for a lube job because I think their &quot;fix&quot; is gonna end up giving us the shaft more than ever, except this time it'll be permanent.  I'll wait and see, but I hope it's a REAL fix they give us and not some pansy utility spells which effect only us and not our dmg output and then call us balanced.  I think EVERYONE agrees (even the classes that think they have problems like the necro's who hate their DoT's not sticking on uber mobs and only doing 66% dmg if the mob isn't rooted) that the wizard is least desirable in a group and in high lvl xp groups, if accepted people often wish they'd taken someone else, I want this to change because I LOVE my WIZARD, I just HATE that no one else thinks he's useful and when I sit back and look at him, I have to agree to a point.  (BTW Did you know druids now have forms of clarity? and no not this cheap manaskin clarity, at 60 they get a spell that gives them close to a full clarity effect plus other buffs it's called PoG (Protection of the Glades) check it out.<br>
<br>
Yaldin<br>
