Absor's posts all state that any changes to our class cannot infringe upon the abilities of other classes.  If the wizards are to be so narrowly focused, that focus should apply equally to every pure class.  <br>
<br>
Go swing that sword, tankboy...but keep your grubby hands out of my casting realm. <p><a href="http://www.elddarcaste.com/"target="web"><img src="http://www.elddarcaste.com/sigfile1.jpg" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umitebe1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MiteBe1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/15/01 10:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WOW Melee's are casters too now!!!</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I find it kinda ironic that it's ok for melee classes to get crosse class abilities but god forbid that they should give Int casters a clarity item or a decent heal item. Their fear of soloing is unreasonable and I feel is driving these decisions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=quiksilver1>Quiksilver1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/15/01 5:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> thanks guys (=</span><hr size=1> hehe thanks for making my post intelligible, I actually should have posted this in the rant forum, but yes that's my point, they get class specific items that give them other classes abilities, why not give me a robe with feign death on it huh?  oh wait, they gave casters a haste robe from jumpy in old seb, my mistake what was I thinking!!<br>
