<br>
Now, my point is this.  When you get to lvl 60, what do you have to look onward to?  New items?  Maybe.  New lvls and abilities and creatures?  No.   Therefore IMHO, lvl 60 is the end of EVERquest.  Now, i'm not lvl 60 yet, but I know from experience with other games that no mater how much fun I was having before, after I've beat the last level, a good portion of the fun is gone.  I've stopped playing my favorite games just because they've been beaten and there's no more challenge in doing it again.<br>
<br>
Verant is not directly opposed to anybody playing solo.<br>
Verant is directly opposed to anybody stopping playing.<br>
They fear that the faster people reach 60, the faster they'll stop playing and stop PAYING.  Hmmm, seems like at last count there were over 300,000 EQ players, each paying $10 per month.  That's $36,000,000 annualy.  If I was making that kind of money, I wouldn't wanna help people finish the game either.<br>
<br>
